Since the beginning of 2019, members of the National Assembly of France have introduced 29 bills pertaining to the French Bioethics Law, which is revised every seven years. These bills have asked the government to establish a department to register human organ transplants, tracking the sources of organs from foreign countries, and enacting more dissuading punishment to curb organ trafficking.

More and more evidence found in recent years has identified China as the major source of organ trafficking and removal of organs from people without consent.

snippet.textDisplay: You can blame the board and the Glazers all you want, but Solskjaer's woes are his own doing, playing a 4 2 3 1 irrespective of the opposition instead of realizing this squad is built to play a 4 4 2 or a 3 5 2. If Solskjaer had an iota of coaching acumen, he'd have realized that a long time ago and retained Lukaku, Young and Smalling, allowing him to get the results he needs to keep his job and complete his rebuild. Played the right way, Lukaku would have guaranteed him 20+ goals a season, Young would have solved is winger/wingback problem, and Smalling would have done his bit defensively. Simply put, Solskjaer downfall is down to his incompetence as a manager, signing a one-dimensional winger, an offensively limited fullback, and a slow, cumbersome center half instead of just keeping what he had and getting the most out of them.
